<p style="text-align: justify;">This is where the difference happens. OSAB is an organization compiling students that participate in BYU-Idaho online programs and courses. These students give their input concerning the BYU-Idaho online experience through taking short surveys once a month and meeting one hour a month in online gatherings where you can help participate in influencing the school with more efficient growth. Your participation will&nbsp;help&nbsp;courses&nbsp;be a wonderful experience for everyone involved. You Make the Difference.</p>
<p><img alt="OSAB Cycle" height="450" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/icons/OSAB cycle.jpg" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="456" /><br /><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
<div style="text-align: justify;">By clicking "Apply" you will be taken to our first survey where you will be given two opportunities to sign up to help with OSAB. The first service opportunity involves taking 10-15 minute surveys once a month.&nbsp; These surveys will be sent at the beginning of the month and the feedback you provide will be instrumental in making the online experience the best it can be. The second service opportunity takes it a step further and allows you, in just one more hour a month, to meet online with other students and have discussions to further the administration's understanding about the online experience for students. These meetings will be on the 3rd Thursday of the month (times will vary).</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
